content:
Human-rated Examples:
Example 1:
Text: Grappler-I'm not sure if this article is OK now or not. What do you think?
Annotation from annotator: 11

Example 2:
Text: That's reason to expand the treatment to other painters, not to blank this one.  And you didn't think that there would be more articles on van Gogh paintings?
Annotation from annotator: 3

Example 3:
Text: Alistair, you have only undone the autoblock; you haven't unblocked the account yet. Could you do that, please?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 4:
Text: Actually it was a compliment. Does that count as an 'issue'?
Annotation from annotator: 7

Example 5:
Text: Could you please explain <url> to me? I don't see how deleting a person's userpage is correct?
Annotation from annotator: 9

Example 6:
Text: And  what did I do wrong???????????????????????
Annotation from annotator: 3

Example 7:
Text: Hi.  Why did you blank the redirect at <url>?
Annotation from annotator: 7

Example 8:
Text: I'm sorry, but there is no discussion on the talk page that indicates that there was a debate about renaming, so the keep vote stands, I'm afraid.  There were nine votes to keep, and only one to merge, so I don't understand how a single vote trumps nine others?
Annotation from annotator: 10

Example 9:
Text: I understand your point about MJ being very close and having competent editors, but do you not think those of us who understand the source problems, etc. that the Reagan page is having should try and explain them to those editors (that is, try to educate them)?
Annotation from annotator: 6

Example 10:
Text: About your last edit to <url>.  Do you have a source?
Annotation from annotator: 10

Example 11:
Text: Could you please explain to me what the buttons do? How do you "Not accept" a change, that's what...you revert it, don't you...?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 12:
Text: Hello Jeffq, I noticed you revert vandalism occasionally. Would you like me to grant your account <url> to help you revert vandalism more easily?
Annotation from annotator: 18

Example 13:
Text: that hotcat lockup, was like an edit conflict, so i tried a backup and re-enter.  thanks for the assistance, i'm using the old layout, so would the new view affect my hotcat category edits?
Annotation from annotator: 12

Example 14:
Text: Hi, I see you voted "support" but in the neutral section. Would you like to move that to the support section?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 15:
Text: I found an autoblock and cleared it.  Can you edit now?
Annotation from annotator: 9

Example 16:
Text: The file above does not meet the <url> so as to be copyrighted or eligible for fair use, as I had stated so on <url> when I first moved it there. What issues should be resolved?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 17:
Text: Upon further thought, maybe I could look through lists of deleted articles to see if any interest me and see if I can bring them back (with adequate sourcing). Do you know anything about that process?
Annotation from annotator: 10

Example 18:
Text: It does not appear to have attracted any participants other than Gerda. Perhaps adding a <person> template would draw in more participants?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 19:
Text: Excuse me? What are you accusing me of doing?
Annotation from annotator: 3

Example 20:
Text: Here's the FFD page: <url>. How do you know that the photograph was made pursuant to a law or ordinance or in connection with the transaction of official business?
Annotation from annotator: 11

Example 21:
Text: That "guest" could have been an undercover Colbert staff member and the whole segment could have been staged. Otherwise, why would Colbert have taken 3 minutes out of his show to talk to someone in the audience?
Annotation from annotator: 6

Example 22:
Text: <url> needs urdu script for the name of the subject (Bangla script has already been added). Can you help?
Annotation from annotator: 9

Example 23:
Text: Hello. Since you have contributed to <url> in the past, could you spare a minute to discuss the fate of <url>?
Annotation from annotator: 14

Example 24:
Text: Many people have mentioned this mythical facillity - I've never found it, and assumed it was only available to sysops, which I am not. Is this the case?
Annotation from annotator: 7

Example 25:
Text: Sure, but what's the deal with fair use and cropping?  I thought the Zatanna one got removed?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 26:
Text: Like most users with their articles screwed over by <url>'s new web facelift, I'm at a lost with <url> being dead. Can you help?
Annotation from annotator: 11

Example 27:
Text: Question: how do we move the content from the existing page to the new page?  How do we reference the space to the new page?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 28:
Text: I can't find a notice on the source website saying that this image is under a creavtive commons lisence. DO you have email corespondance or something?
Annotation from annotator: 10

Example 29:
Text: COI? What COI do you think I have?
Annotation from annotator: 7

Example 30:
Text: Done. I may have missed a few links when copying them across, so could you please look through it just in case?
Annotation from annotator: 15

Estimated Examples:
Example 1:
Text: Since I have no purpose I don't need to use wikipedia, so can you change my username to <url> (<url>)???
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 2:
Text: <url> and <url> seem to be two articles on the same subject.  What's the point of having separate articles?
Annotation from annotator: 0

Example 3:
Text: I have a quick question for you (I'm asking now since I am sure that this is going to be brought up either at the ACR or the FAC, when I finally get there): you've added a "pp." for the citation given for the national defense authorization act of 2007, but the rest of the article makes use of the "p." system. Shouldn't the "pp." be changed to a "p." for conformity, or is the use of the "pp." correct from the perspective of citation guidelines?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 4:
Text: All my edits to clear Lloyd George disappeared from the running count. They haven't been undone, is this a bug?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 5:
Text: 4. I had once felt that the Euroleague, Italian and Greek leagues were the top leagues. If I were to choose selected European leagues from this page <url>, do you have any thoughts on which ones are important?
Annotation from annotator: 20

Example 6:
Text: I noticed that you twice placed a request for citation on the <url> page,<url> <url>, but it was silently removed by <url> <url>. I've removed the sentence altogether; do you think any other action should be taken at this point?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 7:
Text: Hello -- I see you changed a couple of entries relating to "PALATINE, the Subject Centre for Dance, Drama and Music of the UK Higher Education Academy".  I don't know (or even care) why that organisation chooses to refer to itself by capitalising the word, but (and I ask for information here) is there a policy that precludes us from respecting that choice?
Annotation from annotator: 4

Example 8:
Text: Hi, you've done a lot of work on comparing FA country articles. Are you aware of any country that got special praise for the selection of images in the article?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Example 9:
Text: I think this is a clear case of <url> . What do you think?
Annotation from annotator: 8

Example 10:
Text: I think I'm gonna request a free image from a Wikipedia biography subject by following <url>. I was wondering, if I'm planning to upload the image to Commons and the subject doesn't speak English to understand the e-mail, what should I do?
Annotation from annotator: 1

Example 11:
Text: What?!  Why did you resolve this without dealing with the User I mentioned?
Annotation from annotator: 3

Example 12:
Text: Hi, noticed you removed categories on defunct/renamed schools. Why do you think them unnecessary?
Annotation from annotator: 13

Target Example:
Text: See email first. Is this coming from somewhere or something particular?
